Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 6 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Mongolia 
in the last two years is paying a great attention to the 
strengthening of the country's customs service, providing it 
with new technical means. 
  As the deputy-chairman of the Central Custom's Department of 
Mongolia Ya. Erhembayar informed the MONTSAME correspondent, the 
customs service on the whole is provided with computers and 
other technical means, and in the first quarter of the current 
year the work on switching them to the united network with 
centralized control panel will be accomplished. In the new year 
the works will be continued on the international project 
"asicuda" on workout customs information. To raise 
qualification and professional skill of customs inspectors the 
training courses are organized within the country and abroad, he 
said. 

